# SANDCASTLE.md (EXAMPLE — copy to `SANDCASTLE.md` to activate the gates)

**The critique-as-gate and skill-discipline gates are DORMANT by default.**
The sandcastle template ships without a real `SANDCASTLE.md`, so
`parseRequiredSkillsByType` finds no type sections, every issue's
`requiredSkills` is `undefined` (or `[]` for a type that explicitly lists none), and both gates graceful-degrade to a no-op.
Nothing is graded until you create this file.

To activate: copy this file to `SANDCASTLE.md` at your repo root, then edit the
`type:<label>` sections below so each GitHub issue type label maps to the design
principles (Skill names) it must satisfy. A principle is enforced two ways:
the implementer must invoke `Skill(<name>)` (skill-discipline gate), and the
diff must pass the critique sub-agent graded against `<name>`'s rubric
(critique-as-gate). A principle's rubric is loaded from
`.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` (repo-local) or `~/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`
(global) — if NONE of a type's principles have a loadable rubric, the issue is
quarantined rather than silently shipped (ADR 0006 v3 fail-loud preflight).
Delete this `# SANDCASTLE.md (EXAMPLE…)` title line after copying.

**`Required:` bullets under a `type:X` section MUST be headless-runnable
skills.** A tool that needs a live running app or external credentials (e.g.
`verify`) must be attached via a `tool:` label / `Opt in via tool:` block
below, never as a `type:`-section `Required:` bullet — the parser that builds
the host skill-discipline gate's required-skill list deliberately skips
`tool:` bullets, so a tool listed correctly under `Opt in via tool:` never
reaches that gate at all. List it under `Required:` instead and the host gate
will quarantine the issue before the reviewer's unrunnable-tool carve-out
(review-prompt.md) ever gets a chance to apply.

**Install a rubric for every principle you list**, or that type's issues will be
quarantined. The `type:new-component` example below lists `impeccable` and
`layout`, so a verbatim copy quarantines your first `type:new-component` issue
until you add those `SKILL.md` files (repo-local or `~/.claude/skills/`) or swap
in principles you already have.

### type:new-component

Required:

- impeccable
- layout

Opt in via `tool:` labels for optional, non-graded tooling.

### type:cleanup

Required: (none)

`type:cleanup` declares zero principles, so it ships without grading — use it
for pure deletions / mechanical refactors.
